According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global PET Bottle Recycling Solution Market was valued at USD 5 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 12 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 9% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing robust growth as governments, brand owners, and recycling companies intensify efforts to reduce plastic waste and strengthen circular economy initiatives. Rising regulatory mandates for recycled content, increasing investments in advanced recycling technologies, and growing corporate sustainability commitments are accelerating the adoption of PET bottle recycling solutions worldwide. As demand for high-quality recycled polyethylene terephthalate (rPET) continues to exceed supply, companies are rapidly expanding recycling infrastructure and adopting innovative technologies to improve efficiency and product quality.
